That is very powerful, and why
don't we teach to that strength,

00:30:43.360 --> 00:30:45.940
that uniqueness that they bring
instead of to their weakness?

00:30:45.940 --> 00:30:49.570
When we teach to the child's
weakness, their inability to hear,

00:30:49.570 --> 00:30:52.510
we take away from what we can
give them, and we instead teach

00:30:52.510 --> 00:30:56.390 position:56%
to their ability to have that visual
language, and why not do both?

00:30:56.390 --> 00:30:59.080
Why not afford them both
that opportunity to speak,

00:30:59.080 --> 00:31:01.630
have access to that language
as well as sign language?

00:31:01.630 --> 00:31:04.340
And ADA is an invitation
for us to engage

00:31:04.340 --> 00:31:06.640
in that kind of a conversation.

00:31:08.260 --> 00:31:09.980
Moving on to employment.

00:31:09.980 --> 00:31:12.890
That's the key to a strong country.

00:31:15.180 --> 00:31:18.260
Deaf people's success in the
United States has been afforded

00:31:18.260 --> 00:31:21.700
by their access to
employment opportunities.

00:31:22.710 --> 00:31:28.150 position:56%
Many Gallaudet graduates go into
the workforce, and strangely enough,

00:31:28.150 --> 00:31:30.920
in the last 10 to 15 years,

00:31:30.920 --> 00:31:34.090
our progress in the employment
arena is not been as great

00:31:34.090 --> 00:31:39.660 position:56%
as it had been before the passage of
the ADA, and the question is raised

00:31:39.660 --> 00:31:43.090
as to why that is the case.

00:31:43.090 --> 00:31:44.970
What's the fundamental
problem that we need

00:31:44.970 --> 00:31:47.890
to address in order to change that?

00:31:47.890 --> 00:31:51.730 position:56%
Minnesota and the federal government
in the past looked to the number

00:31:51.730 --> 00:31:54.980
of people with disabilities and
saw that's over 20, 15 to 20,

00:31:54.980 --> 00:31:57.910
30 percent of these
individuals-never 30,

00:31:57.910 --> 00:32:01.590
but at least 15 to 20 percent
of the population is disabled.

00:32:01.590 --> 00:32:08.670
After 2007, after the recession,
the numbers began to drop off to 2

00:32:08.670 --> 00:32:13.030
to 7 percent of the disability
community being employed,

00:32:13.030 --> 00:32:15.340
and this creates the
future challenge for us.

00:32:15.340 --> 00:32:17.070
Our work is not done.

00:32:17.070 --> 00:32:20.020
We sit back and look to the
wonder of ADA, and, yes,

00:32:20.020 --> 00:32:22.950
certainly we do recognize that,
but we also recognize the work

00:32:22.950 --> 00:32:26.110
that needs to be done and what
we need to do in order to change

00:32:26.110 --> 00:32:29.590
and improve our employment
outcome for all people

00:32:29.590 --> 00:32:36.770
with disabilities,
not just deaf people.

00:32:36.770 --> 00:32:40.350
Learning and engagement in
the community is our right,

00:32:40.350 --> 00:32:42.700
and that's a lesson that
we learned from the ADA.

00:32:42.700 --> 00:32:46.410
We have a right to learn and be
engaged in the community around us,

00:32:46.410 --> 00:32:50.220
and that's what leads to us
being strong citizens-engaged

00:32:50.220 --> 00:32:53.550
in the political process and
our communities and our schools

00:32:53.550 --> 00:32:56.620
and our family units, and
our deaf organizations,

00:32:56.620 --> 00:32:59.950
and a variety of other places.

00:33:13.260 --> 00:33:16.600
Access. If we talk about
access, it is public good.

00:33:16.600 --> 00:33:19.740
I mean don't think it
only being about you

00:33:19.740 --> 00:33:23.200
as an individual having access,
but it is in overall public good

00:33:23.200 --> 00:33:26.850
and applies to every single one of
our us-- our families, our friends,

00:33:26.850 --> 00:33:29.160
our communities around us.

00:33:29.160 --> 00:33:30.460
Providing interpreters

00:33:30.460 --> 00:33:32.720
and captioning is not
just advantageous

00:33:32.720 --> 00:33:34.020
for people who are deaf.

00:33:34.020 --> 00:33:36.000
It's advantageous for
everyone in the room.

00:33:36.000 --> 00:33:40.150
It is about public good, and that
kind of language needs to change,

00:33:40.150 --> 00:33:42.250
and that is the impact of the ADA.

00:33:42.250 --> 00:33:44.580
We must choose to broaden
the understanding

00:33:44.580 --> 00:33:46.700
of the impact of the ADA.

00:33:46.700 --> 00:33:52.670
It provides access, and that
